latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Yesterday I did an ‘Ask me anything’ on my story, not realising how the questions would bring out so much that I had buried inside.

To those who don’t know me or only recently followed me, I lost my grandfather in Dec 2021. He was my best friend and a person I called home. Because of his dementia he didn’t really remember who I was very well, so we’d just sing instead, every day. And sing till a point that I’d often beg to leave. But he was a man of patience. He gave me my time to warm up to it, he also let me butcher all the varnams with my loud guitaring, and reluctantly cooperate when I’d bring Kaju my cat into the room. For me it was less about becoming a better singer and more about showing up in whatever capacity so he could sing with his perakutty. I was never attached to singing, and now I can’t imagine a life without it- because that would mean a life without him. 

The AMAs yesterday asked me about how I’m always so happy and full of infectious energy and all I could think of in that moment was how tired I’d become in putting up that façade. A part of me died with Thatha, which was natural, but I can no longer tell what pains me more- the grief or the fatigue from stopping myself from grieving. I’ve watched myself torture the part of me that’s still alive for not being able to function effectively and for breaking down in public or at the most inconvenient timings. Such a bully!

Soooo I’m sharing this video because this was a very empowering moment for me, and while it’s not a ‘bouncing with joy Eshna’, this is my honest version of happiness. Every single time before this video whenever I’d sense an incoming breakdown I would either go into fight or flight mode. I’m proud that I stuck around and sang till the end, and that the voice only got louder and stronger. ‘No more begging to leave thathagaaru, this time I’m here to stay.’ Even tho I’m not literally doing better, I’ve gotten so much better at swimming peacefully through the tough days, just like in this video. :)

Okay here’s the deal now guys! This month, you made me taste what hooping with a community felt like- and now I REFUSE to do it alone from here on. The more you give, the more I shall. So, more of this?

Tis a snippet from Hoop Flo’s Launch Party! Yes we threw a party y’all ✨✨Sharing stage with this hero @divya_easwaran who hooped for 4 days of her life and still kicked ass!

But yes folks, before I get into shooting hoop tutorials, I think it’s fair to show you how to assemble your hoop first, especially for your #wheremyhooptravels days! :)

More hoop hacks and hoop care tips coming up soon! But I dare you to sit through 8mins of this first.

Never in my life have I met someone  who I’ve never witnessed sulk or show anger or be bitter. I don’t think he even knew how to be any of those. I miss squishing him for the perpetual smile he always had on his face. He sang and laughed his way through Cancer, getting Covid TWICE, 4 toe amputations, countless leg operations and one of the worst head falls for his age. I’ve never met anyone who’s been in so much pain but made you believe that nothing is more painful than not finding joy in life and its precious moments. I whine, I overthink, I get anxious, I get worked up when I get sick, and I hardly celebrate victories- and then I walk across to his room, and see him be this person in this video ALL the time. I’ve been feeling homesick lately because of actually being away from home, but right now I think it’s synonymous to missing that hug.

Did I design this course so I could low-key teach you how to eat while hooping? Possibly! Last year we gave you The Basics of Upper Body Hooping! This year, make 2022 exciting now with The Basics of Lower Body Flo! (In other words, learn to hoop on your knees, thighs, ankles, and travel the hoop up to your waist!)

Both The Basics courses are open for enrolment! AND they come free with the Winter Gift Box (link in bio) 🎁

✂️: @rohanjhnsn

From thatha’s Prayer Meet day before. We sang, danced, clapped, and remembered him in the happiest of ways! He’ll be overjoyed to know that the jugalbandi has been passed down to the chacha :) 

I can hear him correcting my Ni and Sa. But it’s helping me become aware of my notes being sung half step down too. Anybody out here who teaches Carnatic music? I think it’s time to formally train. 🙊

Adhi thala varnam: Mohanam

I won’t find someone like him though.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Sound on! I’m grateful that I have a place I can share my story through my movement and my words, and that you choose to listen. To be seen and heard is the greatest gift you can give me. Thankyou. It makes me so curious about your journeys and perspectives. I have so much to learn from you. What are the things you’re moved by, why do you do what you do, what’s your purpose? I hope I get to meet you someday (however awkward I may be and in turn make you too). But until then, stick around here and let’s rediscover a few things together x (stick around longer and I’ll promise to bring this hoop to you too, since you’ve been asking)

This is a beautiful film I shot for @tatacliqluxury . I hope I get to collaborate with as much honesty as I got to here, in the future. You’ve set a bit of a benchmark for me now with the work I want to put out. Even Thatha will be so proud.

What happens when you hand a bunch of girlies some hula hoops on a once-in-a-lifetime kind of trip? 

They surprise you — with how much fun they have, how quickly they learn, and just how loud it can get 😆 
We had hoopers at all skill levels but watching these enthu hoopers go from 0 to 100 in less than a week has left us feeling so proud🥹

The future of hooping feels bright, and in very good hands.

latestPosts.caption:
EAT. HOOP. LOVE. 
Bali, May 2025 🌺💫

Where do I even begin?

There’s something so joyful and infectious about witnessing adults—especially women—just play. Like really play.
Hooping in pools, dancing at waterfalls, cheering each other on, saying YES to everything from fire hooping to karaoke nights to surfing.

My heart’s still so full. Thank you for reminding me how fun, freeing, and deeply special this work can be.
The first one will always be unforgettable 💛 

Shot by the amazing @notyoureffy 
Shoutout to @theexperience.co for jumping on board and to @hoopingmad for coming along! ❤️

Go follow @eat.hoop.love for your daily dose of nature and play. Dates for the next edition will be out soon. ✨

My celebration after wrapping up a 7-day hoop retreat in Bali was to do a victory lap in the ocean.
In hindsight, catching up on sleep might’ve been the healthier choice than paddling for hours, for days under the sun.
And just when my shoulders thought it was over, I did my PADI Open Water Dive Course—because why stop at one immersive experience when you can do three? :’)

Retreat content starts tomorrow. Follow @eat.hoop.love to see what actually went down ✨💛

What photos of you are still ahead of their time?

I shot this in 2022 and couldn’t get myself to post it back then. How absolutely silly of me!
I think photos like these, where I looked confident beyond measure felt… disorienting. Also—as a newbie @nike sponsor (been with them 3 yrs now tho) receiving a bunch of sick gear for this NYC shoot felt too huge a deal for where my self-esteem was at the time.
But it’s 2025 now, and I can say I look fiyaaah! Can’t believe @djenedesigns captured a version of me I wasn’t quite ready to meet yet. And that hair situation is completely a creation of hers! 
It’s wild how a photograph can hold space for your becoming. And how a banger song like Missy Elliot’s Work It can somehow just fit!

Thank you @djenedesigns, too much love for you! Also for your patience 😅
